## Backstory

Have Heart is a straight edge hardcore punk band from New Bedford, Massachusetts. They formed in 2002 and released two full-length albums: *The Things We Carry (2006)* and *Songs to Scream at the Sun (2008)*. *Songs to Scream at the Sun* received critical acclaim and was chosen as "album of the year" on many hardcore-oriented sites as well as landing at No. 193 on the Billboard top 200.

Have Heart's lyrical themes focus on self-image, the straight edge lifestyle, pressure, self-destruction, friendship, and family. Although the band broke up in 2009 after their final show on [National Edge Day](https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/National_Edge_Day) they reformed in 2015 with four of the original five member line-up. They've changed their name to Free stating that they did not want to take "the spotlight" away from younger hardcore bands. As Free they've released a four-track demo in 2015 and an EP titled Ex *Tenebris* in May 2017. You can listen to the four-track 2015 demo and Ex Tenebris at bandcamp for free here:

- [Free - Demo 2015](https://freehc.bandcamp.com/album/demo-2015)
- [Free - Ex Tenebris](https://freehc.bandcamp.com/album/ex-tenebris)

